de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.clustering

Class ClusteringObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.clustering.ClusteringObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArealClusteringObject, TemporalClusteringObject

    public abstract class ClusteringObject
extends java.lang.Object
    This abstract class is a simple data class for sorting data by the OPTICS-OF algorithm. Methods regarding the distance between to ClusteringObjects have to be implemented by subclasses. The only complex methods in this class are the ones for setting the local reachability density and the outlier factor used for the OPTICS OF algorithm. These are set in setLocalReachabilityDensity(double, int) respectively setOutlierFactor(int).
    Since:
    27.01.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:
    #setCoreDistance(SortedSet, int), setLocalReachabilityDensity(double, int), setOutlierFactor(int), getDistance(ClusteringObject)

      • setCoreDistance

        public abstract void setCoreDistance(int minNeighbors)
        This abstract method has to be implemented by a subclass. It calculates the core distance which is defined as minimal distance for which the ClusteringObject still is a core object (has at least minNeighbors in this distance).
        Parameters:
        minNeighbors - - an int value which represents the minimal count of neighbors for the object to be a core object.

      • setLocalReachabilityDensity

        public void setLocalReachabilityDensity(double neighborsReachabilitySum,
                               int minNeighbors)
        This method calculates the local reachability densitiy of the ClusteringObject. This value represents the inverse of the average reachability distance from the minNeighbors-nearest-neighbors of the ClusteringObject.
        Parameters:
        neighborsReachabilitySum - - a double value which represents the sum of the reachability distances of the minNeighbors-nearest-neighbors.
        minNeighbors - - an int value which represents the minimal needed neighbors for the ClusteringObject to be a core object.

      • getLocalReachabilityDensity

        public double getLocalReachabilityDensity()

      • setOutlierFactor

        public void setOutlierFactor(int minNeighbors)
        This method calculates the outlier factor of the ClusteringObject. This value represents the average of the ratios of the local reachability densities of the minNeighbors-nearest-neighbors and the ClusteringObject. If a cluster is of uniform density this factor should be close around 1, because the local reachability densities are identical.
        Parameters:
        minNeighbors - - an int value which represents the minimal needed neighbors for the ClusteringObject to be a core object.

        public abstract double getDistance(ClusteringObject destinationObject)
        This abstract method has to be implemented by a subclass. It calculates and returns the distance form this ClusteringObject to the given destinationObject.
        Parameters:
        destinationObject - - a arbitrary ClusteringObject.
        Returns:
